          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "(x²+2x+3)(x+1) = x³+x²+2x²+2x+3x+3 = x³+3x²+5x+3."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch09_B_009",
          "text": "Find the product: (2x + y)(2x - y)(4x² + y²)",
          "options": {
            "a": "16x⁴ - y⁴",
            "b": "4x² - y²",
            "c": "16x⁴ + y⁴",
            "d": "4x⁴ - y⁴"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "(2x+y)(2x-y) = 4x²-y². Then (4x²-y²)(4x²+y²) = (4x²)²-(y²)² = 16x⁴-y⁴."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch09_B_010",
          "text": "Using identity, evaluate: 9.8 × 10.2",
